  "prompt": "How is Hired's referral rate?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, specific details about Hired.com's referral rates\u2014such as the percentage of users who refer others to the platform or the success rate of those referrals\u2014are not publicly disclosed. Hired does offer various features and programs to engage its community, which may include referral incentives or rewards, but the exact metrics and performance of these programs are typically internal data.\n\nIf you're interested in Hired's referral program or specific referral rates, I recommend the following steps:\n\n1. **Visit Hired's Official Website:** Check their [referral program page](https://hired.com/) (if available) for any publicly shared details or updates about referral incentives and success metrics.\n\n2. **Contact Hired Support:** Reach out directly to Hired's customer support or your account representative. They can provide the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding referral rates and any associated programs.\n\n3. **Community Forums and Reviews:** Platforms like LinkedIn, Glassdoor, or other professional forums may have discussions where users share their experiences with Hired's referral programs. While not official, these can offer valuable insights.\n\n4. **Press Releases and News Articles:** Occasionally, companies release performance metrics or program successes through press releases or in interviews. Searching recent news might yield relevant information.\n\nIf you're considering participating in Hired's referral program or leveraging referrals for recruiting or job searching, reaching out directly to Hired will provide the most reliable and tailored information.",
